ent.=C2=A0
But a 9-figure valuation for a one-year-old company suggests investors see =
something beyond mere efficiency gains.=C2=A0
I think it=E2=80=99s this: Rox is using the fact that companies are willing=
 to buy AI as a foot in the door to prove usefulness to get more data and i=
ntegrations to build the system of record and earn customer trust and usage=
 and learn so that Rox is ready when AI gets really good.
This isn=E2=80=99t just good strategy, it=E2=80=99s grand strategy.=C2=A0
In On Grand Strategy [ https://substack.com/redirect/9c78431b-2e54-4469-8e6=
0-b3d520aca0d6?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8E=
xkRNpU ], John Lewis Gaddis defines the term as =E2=80=9Cthe alignment of p=
otentially unlimited aspirations with necessarily limited capabilities.=E2=
=80=9D
Grand strategy requires an honest assessment of those limited capabilities =
as they are today, not as you want them to be.=C2=A0
=E2=80=9CNapoleon lost his empire by confusing aspirations with capabilitie=
s; Lincoln saved his country by not doing so.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0
In Rox=E2=80=99s case, the capabilities of AI agents as they stand today ar=
e that they:
Can make sense of unstructured data.
Are excellent customer acquisition tools.=C2=A0
Today, in other words, AI is a means, not an end. A capability, not an aspi=
ration.=C2=A0
Rox=E2=80=99s approach, as Ishan described it, is to =E2=80=9Cbuild whateve=
r you need to build to get companies to feed your system of record.=E2=80=
=9D=C2=A0
Instead of promising agents that will sell for you, they build agents that =
will help you sell.=C2=A0
Instead of helping sellers go after new customers, Rox helps them =E2=80=9C=
go after the most unglamorous piece =E2=80=93 their existing customers.=E2=
=80=9D This, Ishan tells me, is who =E2=80=9C80-90% of revenue comes from.=
=E2=80=9D It=E2=80=99s also who companies have the most data on. And it=E2=
=80=99s the group of companies worst-served by existing systems, which are =
focused on contract-based versus consumption-based sales.=C2=A0
This approach addresses the two big concerns I=E2=80=99ve had about AI appl=
ication companies, turns them into advantages, even.=C2=A0
=E2=80=9CFirst, revenue is easy but potentially not sticky, something I wro=
te about as far back as May 2023 in Small Applications, Growing Protocols [=
 https://substack.com/redirect/79442d3b-2492-4c93-b71f-770900decd64?j=3DeyJ=
1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ].=E2=80=9D
In Rox=E2=80=99s case, AI support agents are the small applications, and th=
e data and workflows are the company=E2=80=99s own =E2=80=9Cprotocol=E2=80=
=9D which gets more valuable with time, integrations, and more applications=
 from Rox itself. Like a protocol, it is open =E2=80=93 companies will buil=
d on Rox if it=E2=80=99s the best place to build, and leave and take their =
data with them if it isn=E2=80=99t.=C2=A0
=E2=80=9CSecond, there is so much uncertainty about how models will improve=
 =E2=80=93 that things are moving so fast =E2=80=93 that it feels like a le=
ap of faith to bet on any one application now. There are dozens, if not hun=
dreds, of GTM AIs in the market today,=E2=80=9D including well-funded ones =
like 11x.
Proving value early and often, incrementally at first, is a way to manufact=
ure increasing returns and path dependence.=C2=A0
Small early wins at high velocity compound. Overpromising and underdeliveri=
ng does not.=C2=A0
So what does Rox promise, and do, today?=C2=A0
Rox=E2=80=99s Current Capabilities
Rox=E2=80=99s product today is straightforward: agents assigned to each of =
a seller=E2=80=99s accounts collect and monitor internal and external data =
and surface the most relevant bits to the seller.=C2=A0
Typically, I would explain exactly what and how the product does, but I thi=
nk Rox=E2=80=99s launch video does a really good job, so I=E2=80=99d encour=
age you to watch it.=C2=A0
Rox doesn=E2=80=99t promise the moon, but it does what it promises. Kiran N=
agra, Ramp=E2=80=99s Sales Leader for Account Management, says in the video=
