an></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 2=
6px;font-size: 16px;">The models aren&#8217;t there yet, but they&#8217;ll =
get there. Everything other than building relationships and educating custo=
mers &#8211; the non-human stuff &#8211; will mostly be delivered by agents=
=2E</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;co=
lor: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26p=
x;font-size: 16px;">The opportunity for Rox is building the best team and b=
est product with tech-forward customers to own the application layer for th=
is as underlying models get good enough to fulfill the grand promises compa=
nies are making about their capabilities today.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"margin=
: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">Thi=
s is another update to my mental model of AI: even as the foundation models=
 themselves get smarter, there&#8217;s reason to believe that there will be=
 a ton of value in the application layer.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0=
;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">Intelligence do=
esn&#8217;t equal usefulness. Here&#8217;s a thought exercise that one of R=
ox&#8217;s investors put to me:&nbsp;</p><blockquote style=3D"border-left: =
4px solid #0c2427;margin: 20px 0;padding: 0;"><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px =
0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16p=
x;"><em><span>If you hired a 160 IQ college grad, they wouldn&#8217;t be ab=
le to do much on Day 1. If you spent a year training them, they could proba=
bly start doing good things. That&#8217;s what the application layer is: gu=
iding super intelligent models to work in context. </span><strong>The broad=
 opportunity at the application layer is building the data and workflows to=
 make AI useful.</strong></em></p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px=
 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">Even in my fi=
rst conversation with Ishan, I was convinced Rox had what it takes to win, =
that by playing the long game, it could build the data and workflows to mak=
e AI useful to sellers.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(=
54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">That&#8217;s why I kept ask=
ing if he had a hard stop, so I could flood him with questions about the fu=
ture he saw so clearly, the one that he&#8217;s working to bring about.&nbs=
p;</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26=
px;font-size: 16px;"><span>One category of questions was, essentially, </sp=
an><strong>if everyone uses Rox, is there any alpha in Rox?</strong><span>&=
nbsp;</span></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-=
height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">If every company had access to really smart,=
 really useful sales agents, wouldn&#8217;t the advantage disappear?&nbsp;<=
/p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;=
font-size: 16px;">Wouldn&#8217;t the customers just get hit with the same p=
erfectly targeted messages at the same perfect time?&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"m=
argin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;=
">Wouldn&#8217;t customers just be overwhelmed with equally good messages a=
nd ignore all of them?</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55,=
 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><span>Would all sales just be bots=
 selling to bots based on product specs? Wouldn&#8217;t developer</span><em=
> </em><span>agents working with sales agents just build solutions tailored=
 to those specs?&nbsp;</span></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(=
54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">What are us humans going to=
 do with ourselves when the AI takes our jobs?&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"margin:=
 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">Pull=
ing me out of my existential tailspin, Ishan told me he believes that there=
 will inevitably be winners and losers.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20=
px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><span>&#822=
0;</span><strong>The alpha will be an arbitrage on information</strong><spa=
n>: what information you have about your customers and how proactive you ar=
e in using it,&#8221; he explained.&nbsp;</span></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">Informat=
ion is half the battle &#8211; the best companies will have more and better=
 customers, so they&#8217;ll have more and better information, and their ad=
vantage will compound.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(5=
4, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">The other half is what you d=
o with it. For that, the human element remains.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 =
20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">&#8220;No=
n-killers are going to go away,&#8221; he predicts, &#8220;and killers are =
going to be supercharged. It&#8217;s the same with companies: I do believe =
that there is a class of companies that will not survive.&#8221;&nbsp;</p><=
p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font=
-size: 16px;">What will those companies look like?&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"mar=
gin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">=
<strong>&#8220;You need to judge by the person driving the bus.&#8221;</str=
ong><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55=
, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">The world in which Rox succeeds i=
s not a world in which humans disappear. It is a world in which humans are =
amplified, for better or worse.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;col=
or: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">Rox will succeed be=
cause Ishan and the small, exceptional team he&#8217;s built will wield age=
nts to amplify their human strengths.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px=
 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">The Acquired =
framing is useful here: companies are just founders extended. Great compani=
es are force multipliers on their founders&#8217; vision and capabilities.&=
nbsp;</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height:=
 26px;font-size: 16px;"><span>With tools like Rox, </span><em>everyone</em>=
<span> will be extended. Agents will be force multipliers on your vision an=
d capabilities.&nbsp;</span></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(5=
4, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">What became clear to me earl=
y in my conversations with Ishan is that Rox is a master class in Applied A=
I strategy: how to manufacture path dependence by taking the long view and =
matching current capabilities to future aspirations.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"m=
argin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;=
">What&#8217;s become clear to me writing this piece is that those same les=
sons might apply to people, too.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;co=
lor: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">A world full of hi=
ghly capable agents is coming. The best will get better. But you know it&#8=
217;s coming. You can make your own luck if you take the long view and doub=
le-down on your unique capabilities today in anticipation of their future a=
mplification.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55=
);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">Pretty heady stuff for a piece on bor=
ing CRM software!</p><div style=3D"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;"><hr =
style=3D"margin: 32px 0;padding: 0;height: 1px;background: #e6e6e6;border: =
none;"></div><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54, 55, 55);line-hei=
ght: 26px;font-size: 16px;">Thanks to Claude for editing and to Ishan, Eric=
, Max, Kiran, and everyone else who shared their insights for this piece! <=
